'''Kazuraki no Kuni no Miyatsuko''' (葛城国造, also read as Kazuraki Kokuzō or Katsuragi Kokuzō) was the ruler of {{ill|Kazuraki Province|ja|葛城国|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (the southwestern part of the Yamato Province under the [[Ritsuryō]] system). They are also referred to as '''Kazuraki Kokuzō'''.

== Overview ==
The {{ill|Sendai Kuji Hongi|ja|先代旧事本紀|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} "Kokuzō Hongi" refers to them as '''Kazuraki no Kuni no Miyatsuko'''.

=== Ancestry ===
According to the "Kokuzō Hongi" in ''Sendai Kuji Hongi,'' Tsurugi no Nekoto, the ancestor of the {{ill|Kazuraki no Atae|ja|葛城直|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, was appointed the first Kazuraki no Kuni no Miyatsuko during the reign of {{ill|Emperor Jimmu|ja|神武天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. The ''{{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|ja|新撰姓氏録|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}'' states that Tsurugi no Nekoto was a fifth-generation descendant of {{ill|Takamimusubi|ja|高皇産霊尊|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and a fourth-generation descendant of {{ill|Amaoshitatemi no Mikoto|ja|天押立命|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.

=== Clan ===
The Kazuraki clan (葛城氏, surname: ''Atae''). In {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}'s 12th year (683), the clan was granted the surname ''Muraji'' and later ''Imiki'' in the 14th year. Although the {{ill|Kazuraki clan (Omi)|ja|臣姓葛城氏|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} that prospered in the 5th century descended from {{ill|Takenouchi no Sukune|ja|武内宿禰|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, both lines merged through marriage alliances.

== Territory ==
=== Governing Area ===
The Miyatsuko ruled over the area known at the time as ''Kazuraki Province,'' corresponding to the Kazuraki region in {{ill|Yamato Province|ja|Yamato Province|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (modern-day {{ill|Katsuge District|ja|葛上郡|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Katsushimo District|ja|葛下郡|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}). This includes parts of present-day {{ill|Gose City|ja|御所市|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Yamatotakada City|ja|大和高田市|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, Nara Prefecture.

== Clan Deity ==
The clan deity is unknown. However, the region contains several prominent shrines, including {{ill|Katsuragi Mikami Shrine|ja|葛城御縣神社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Katsuragi Hitokotonushi Shrine|ja|葛城坐一言主神社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, both classified as {{ill|Myōjin-taisha|ja|名神大社|fr|Myōjin Taisha|zh|名神大社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} under the {{ill|Engishiki|ja|延喜式|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.

== Notable Figures ==
* '''{{ill|Aratahiko|ja|荒田彦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}'''
** A figure from the Kofun period. His daughter, {{ill|Kazuhime|ja|葛比売|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, was the mother of {{ill|Katsuragi no Sotsuhiko|ja|葛城襲津彦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} of the imperial Kazuraki clan.

== Descendants ==
* {{ill|Katsuragi no Iwamura|ja|葛城磐村|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}
** A Kofun-period figure. His daughter Hiroko became a consort of {{ill|Emperor Yōmei|ja|用明天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* Unnamed Daughter
** Believed to be the wife of {{ill|Soga no Iname|ja|蘇我稲目|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and mother of {{ill|Soga no Umako|ja|蘇我馬子|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* {{ill|Katsuragi Yamada Mizuko|ja|葛城山田瑞子|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}
** A figure from the reign of {{ill|Emperor Kinmei|ja|欽明天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, who was dispatched alongside Iname to Kibi Province as an administrator.
* Katsuragi no Atae Abe
** Referenced in wooden tablets unearthed at the Heijō Palace site as ''Kosho District Katsuragi no Atae Abe'' of Etchū Province.

