{{Infobox Japanese clan | name = Kazuraki no Kuni no Miyatsuko | mon = | mon_name = | honsei = {{ill|Kazuraki clan (Kazuraki no Kuni no Miyatsuko)|ja|葛城氏 (葛城国造)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kazuraki clan (Kazuraki no Kuni no Miyatsuko)|qq=}} | founder = {{ill|Tsurugi no Nekoto|ja|剣根命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsurugi no Nekoto|qq=}} | type = {{ill|Kami lineage|ja|神別|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kami lineage|qq=}} ([[:en:Tenjin|Amatsukami]]) | origin = [[:en:Yamato Province|Yamato Province]] | base = Kazuraki (later [[:en:Yamato Province|Yamato Province]]) | notable_figures = See [[#Notable figures]] | branches = {{ill|Kamo clan (Kamo no Asomi)|ja|賀茂朝臣氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamo clan (Kamo no Asomi)|qq=}} }}
'''Kazuraki no Kuni no Miyatsuko''' (葛城国造, also read as Kazuraki Kokuzō or Katsuragi Kokuzō) was the ruler of {{ill|Kazuraki Province|ja|葛城国|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kazuraki Province|qq=}} (the southwestern part of the Yamato Province under the [[Ritsuryō]] system). They are also referred to as '''Kazuraki Kokuzō'''.
== Overview == The [[:en:Kujiki|Sendai Kuji Hongi]] "Kokuzō Hongi" refers to them as '''Kazuraki no Kuni no Miyatsuko'''.
=== Ancestry === According to the "Kokuzō Hongi" in ''Sendai Kuji Hongi,'' Tsurugi no Nekoto, the ancestor of the {{ill|Kazuraki no Atae|ja|葛城直|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kazuraki no Atae|qq=}}, was appointed the first Kazuraki no Kuni no Miyatsuko during the reign of [[:en:Emperor Jimmu|Emperor Jimmu]]. The ''[[:en:Shinsen Shōjiroku|Shinsen Shōjiroku]]'' states that Tsurugi no Nekoto was a fifth-generation descendant of {{ill|Takamimusubi|ja|高皇産霊尊|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takamimusubi|qq=}} and a fourth-generation descendant of {{ill|Amaoshitatemi no Mikoto|ja|天押立命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amaoshitatemi no Mikoto|qq=}}.
=== Clan === The Kazuraki clan (葛城氏, surname: ''Atae''). In {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|qq=}}'s 12th year (683), the clan was granted the surname ''Muraji'' and later ''Imiki'' in the 14th year. Although the {{ill|Kazuraki clan (Omi)|ja|臣姓葛城氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kazuraki clan (Omi)|qq=}} that prospered in the 5th century descended from [[:en:Takenouchi no Sukune|Takenouchi no Sukune]], both lines merged through marriage alliances.
== Territory == === Governing Area === The Miyatsuko ruled over the area known at the time as ''Kazuraki Province,'' corresponding to the Kazuraki region in [[:en:Yamato Province|Yamato Province]] (modern-day {{ill|Katsuge District|ja|葛上郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsuge District|qq=}} and {{ill|Katsushimo District|ja|葛下郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsushimo District|qq=}}). This includes parts of present-day [[:en:Gose, Nara|Gose City]] and [[:en:Yamatotakada, Nara|Yamatotakada City]], Nara Prefecture.
== Clan Deity == The clan deity is unknown. However, the region contains several prominent shrines, including {{ill|Katsuragi Mikami Shrine|ja|葛城御縣神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsuragi Mikami Shrine|qq=}} and {{ill|Katsuragi Hitokotonushi Shrine|ja|葛城坐一言主神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsuragi Hitokotonushi Shrine|qq=}}, both classified as {{ill|Myōjin-taisha|ja|名神大社|fr|Myōjin Taisha|zh|名神大社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Myōjin-taisha|qq=}} under the [[:en:Engishiki|Engishiki]].
== Notable Figures == * '''{{ill|Aratahiko|ja|荒田彦|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Aratahiko|qq=}}''' ** A figure from the Kofun period. His daughter, {{ill|Kazuhime|ja|葛比売|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kazuhime|qq=}}, was the mother of {{ill|Katsuragi no Sotsuhiko|ja|葛城襲津彦|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsuragi no Sotsuhiko|qq=}} of the imperial Kazuraki clan.
== Descendants == * {{ill|Katsuragi no Iwamura|ja|葛城磐村|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsuragi no Iwamura|qq=}} ** A Kofun-period figure. His daughter Hiroko became a consort of [[:en:Emperor Yōmei|Emperor Yōmei]]. * Unnamed Daughter ** Believed to be the wife of [[:en:Soga no Iname|Soga no Iname]] and mother of [[:en:Soga no Umako|Soga no Umako]]. * {{ill|Katsuragi Yamada Mizuko|ja|葛城山田瑞子|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsuragi Yamada Mizuko|qq=}} ** A figure from the reign of [[:en:Emperor Kinmei|Emperor Kinmei]], who was dispatched alongside Iname to Kibi Province as an administrator. * Katsuragi no Atae Abe ** Referenced in wooden tablets unearthed at the Heijō Palace site as ''Kosho District Katsuragi no Atae Abe'' of Etchū Province.
== References == * ''{{ill|Kokushi Daijiten|ja|国史大辞典|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kokushi Daijiten|qq=}}'' ({{ill|Yoshikawa Kōbunkan|ja|吉川弘文館|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yoshikawa Kōbunkan|qq=}}) * {{Cite book|title=Nihon Kodai Shizoku Jinmei Jiten|author=Sakamoto Tarō and Hirano Kunio|publisher=Yoshikawa Kōbunkan}} * ''Nihon Kodaijinmei Jiten'' (Yoshikawa Kōbunkan) * ''Nihonshi Hiro Jiten'' (Yamakawa Shuppansha) * ''{{ill|Shintō Daijiten|ja|神道大辞典|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shintō Daijiten|qq=}}'' (Rinsen Shoten) * [[:en:Prince Toneri|Tōneri Shinnō]], ''[[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]]''
