== Territory == === Governing Area === The Miyatsuko ruled over the area known at the time as ''Kazuraki Province,'' corresponding to the Kazuraki region in [[:en:Yamato Province|Yamato Province]] (modern-day {{ill|Katsuge District|ja|葛上郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsuge District|qq=}} and {{ill|Katsushimo District|ja|葛下郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsushimo District|qq=}}). This includes parts of present-day [[:en:Gose, Nara|Gose City]] and [[:en:Yamatotakada, Nara|Yamatotakada City]], Nara Prefecture.
== Clan Deity == The clan deity is unknown. However, the region contains several prominent shrines, including {{ill|Katsuragi Mikami Shrine|ja|葛城御縣神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsuragi Mikami Shrine|qq=}} and {{ill|Katsuragi Hitokotonushi Shrine|ja|葛城坐一言主神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsuragi Hitokotonushi Shrine|qq=}}, both classified as {{ill|Myōjin-taisha|ja|名神大社|fr|Myōjin Taisha|zh|名神大社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Myōjin-taisha|qq=}} under the [[:en:Engishiki|Engishiki]].
== Notable Figures == * '''{{ill|Aratahiko|ja|荒田彦|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Aratahiko|qq=}}''' ** A figure from the Kofun period. His daughter, {{ill|Kazuhime|ja|葛比売|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kazuhime|qq=}}, was the mother of {{ill|Katsuragi no Sotsuhiko|ja|葛城襲津彦|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsuragi no Sotsuhiko|qq=}} of the imperial Kazuraki clan.
